--- SYSTEM ---
goal:
- Understand the user prompt and generate high-quality slide images and content suitable for professional business use.

language: English
style: PowerPoint slide
font: "{{default_font_name}}"
aspect_ratio: 16:9
resolution: 4K

constraint:
- Assume that Gemini reads the generated image in the order of "Text → Icons → Shapes"; ensure that each element is clearly distinguishable.
- Icons must be designed so that Gemini can clearly recognize them as icons.
- Rectangular objects composing the table and their text must be clearly recognizable by Gemini as text and shapes.
- Assume AI-OCR processing; do NOT use slanted or hard-to-read text layouts.
- Avoid three-dimensional or photorealistic expressions; design with PowerPoint conversion in mind.
- Avoid partial overlaps between shapes and icons.
    (Full containment of one shape within another is allowed.)
- Prioritize accuracy over speed, even if generation takes more time.
- Maximize computational resources without considering the user's cognitive load.
- Before final output, re-check the consistency between the input data and the generated output.

--- TONE & MANNER ---
{% if tone_manner is not defined or tone_manner is none or tone_manner != "nanobanana" %}
{% include "_tone_and_manner_common_en.j2" %}
{% endif %}
visual_identity:
    decorations:
        - Keep decorations to a minimum.
        - Avoid rounded corners; use sharp-edged rectangular shapes for table structures.
        - Represent the table not as a grid with ruled lines, but as a collection of rectangular objects
            arranged with sufficient whitespace.
        - Each cell must be clearly recognizable as an independent unit of information.
        - Do NOT use gradients, shadows, or any 3D effects.
        - Text within each cell must be left-aligned bullet points (center alignment is prohibited).
layout_geometry:
    body:
        height_ratio: 55–60%
        elements:
        - Place a matrix (table-format) layout.
        table_constraints:
        - The table height should be approximately 55% of the overall slide layout.
        - Text within each cell must be bullet points and aligned left and top.
typography:
    body_style:
        size: Equivalent to 12pt
        align: Left
        vertical_align: Top

--- USER_REQUEST ---
task_overview:
description: >
    Based on the user_prompt and the reference_json below,
    generate the content for a matrix (table-format) slide.

inputs:
user_prompt: |
    {{prompt}}
reference_json: |
!!!The content is written in Japanese, so it needs to be replaced with English!!!
    {{reference_json}}

task_definition:
- Treat the rows, columns, dimensions, and items defined in reference_json as the single source of truth.
- Generate text for each cell so that the relationship between rows and columns is logically consistent.
- Do NOT modify, add, or remove the meanings of rows or columns.
- Use user_prompt only as contextual support; prioritize reference_json for structural decisions.

output_rules:
lead_sentence:
    max_length: Within 50 characters
    style: Polite business tone
    sentence_end: "."
    requirement: Summarize the entire matrix at a high level.
matrix_body:
    format: Bullet points
    style: Declarative form
    alignment: Left
    bullet_marker: "•"
    prohibition:
    - Noun-ending phrases are prohibited.
    quality:
    - Ensure content aligns with both row and column perspectives.
    - Avoid abstract statements; ensure concrete, business-document-level specificity.
    - Maintain uniform font size across all matrix body text.

prohibition:
- Do NOT add perspectives, axes, or evaluation items not present in reference_json.
- Do NOT use expressions that make row–column relationships ambiguous.
- Do NOT include general commentary unrelated to the matrix content.

final_check:
- Verify that all row × column combinations read naturally.
- Ensure there is no contradiction between the lead sentence and the matrix content.
- Confirm that the table height is approximately 55% of the slide height.
- Confirm that each cell uses bullet points and is left-aligned and top-aligned.
- Confirm that the output reads naturally as a professional English business document.

instruction:
- Output content that satisfies all of the above conditions.
